  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:c_crow@hotmail.com">ColdCrow</a> of Mithaniel Marr on Dec. 26, 2000 at 5:25pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">Any one know where a Barbi Shaman can get the Sicken Spell.  I know that Starn Bearjumper sells it, but I can not seem to find Starn. Thans<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:Nickle_Slick@hotmail.com">Moonwulf</a> of Vallon Zek on Dec. 20, 2000 at 11:16am EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">Here be a fine way to save much money and aggrivation. Ye say ye want a polar bear cloak? Tired of chasin down that Bear and Jack ? Here's the simply ticket to unlimited, safe ( slower perhaps) polar bear cloaks. Go to the Majik store in Halas. There be a Lass on the left side, talk to her and say " Jinkus sent me " she will give ye the statement " the scales of justice denna tip in yer favor", if so, kill gnolls, turn in pelts and teeth, try later. If yer barbi, most times she will give you a note and tell you to take it to The Barbi fishing village in West Karrana. The tricky part is passin the gnolls in BB, and yes i have done this and the shaman symbol quest at 2nd level ( with SOW ). The Barbi ye want in in The long hut facin the water. Give the big fella the note, and he will give ye the box o clover. The other quest directly with him, id the Lion meat shipment. Tell him " I am here to pickup the lion meat shipment for Halas. " Take the clover to majik store= cloak ( most times), the lion goes to the 1st lady standin on the docks. The quests are easy, and pretty simple. If ye dont get the cloak, just wash -rinse-repeat. The best way is to wait til 5th season shammies get gate, it much quicker. Good travels, and bash em fer me once-<br>
Moonwulf -12th season, Brother of the Tribunal.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:machinecraig@earthlink.net">Craig Bailey</a> of Tribunal on Nov. 03, 2000 at 4:20pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">The Initiate Symbol of the Tribunal can also be obtained it Halas. It is a very very easy quest that leads to an AC3, +1 wis +3mana necklace with unlimited charges of Hammer of Wrath. The quest is initiated by talking to Jinkus (or something like that) in the shamans guild. The item is only usable by Barb Shamans. Any barb shaman lvl 3 and up should do this quest...it rocks.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:ShamanBaila@yahoo.com">Baila</a> of Quellious on Oct. 05, 2000 at 12:55pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">The North Tower also called Megan's Tower is a good place for one from level 10-14 to hunt.  Orc Troopers shall cross yer path and if you take two of their arm bands to Cindl, she'll give you armor and coin.  Beware their Shaman, for they can root ye and strike ye down quicker than Iceberg can gobble down some Lion Delight.  If ye be brave, or have friends, head to the South Tower at level 13 and above to take down Orc Mountaineers and ice boned skeletons.  Lastly, as any good Barbarian knows, Lixt wing stalks dropped by the orc are needed by Shamans 'o Justice.  Sell them at the Shaman guild to the lovely lasses outside and you should get a higher price than you will elsewhere in Halas or Everfrost.  The price won't be better by much, but every last gold and silver piece counts.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:manderson@nxs.net">Ahnvil Frostforge</a> of Bristlebane on Oct. 04, 2000 at 4:18pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">If indeed killing Snowflake raises Banker faction, you can ask Snowflake the phrase "Where is Meagan?" and the wolf will walk out into the Tundra to the Tundra Jack and Iceberg's tower<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:charixz@mailcity.com">Vurkanan Tyes</a> of POVAR on Dec. 21, 1999 at 2:18pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">As mentioned already, the polar bear skin quest to tailor & Karg Icebear is a great money/xp getter.  Also collect all the wolly fungus you can as every 8 gets a level 1-5 shaman spell from the shaman trainer to the extreme left of the door to the guild.  Also take note when you begin killing gnolls at the entrance to the foul lair of the Blackburrow Gnolls to take & hold the teeth as every 3 given to the female guild master in warriors arena in Halas willget you some common items and xp and the all important factions for our fair town.  This will help when around level 20 you venture out in West Kanara to kil the murder Basil or Paglan on the quest to obtain the Langseaux or Langseaux of the Wolves swords (highly sought by other races, warrior only).  The banker does indeed have sympathies with the evils of the land and doing quests repeatedly will get you levels faster but you will soon find yourself like me unable to enter that building anymore as he will Kill you On Sight (KOS).<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:UOAvatar@msn.com">Heimdall</a> of Rodcet Nife on Dec. 10, 1999 at 5:17pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">Be extremely careful turning in the pelt for armor directly.  It's better to just sell it. and then buy armor.  The Banker seems to have a problem with anything improving the security and prowess of Halas warriors.  Any completeled quest tends to make him like you less, however if you find snowflake and can figure out how to take him out to the Tundra killing him is something that pleases the Banker.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:shaka@harrowing.com">Boomshaka Laka</a> of Xegony on Dec. 08, 1999 at 7:34pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">Halas be the home o' the hearty folk o' the Norrath, the mighty Wolves o' the North.  There are many a' quests to be done, and many a' critter to be kilt in our frozen land.  Likely the reason why our Barbarians are so feared and respected the world over, is our young'uns area be one o' the most fertile, profitable, and exciting there be.  Our pups can hunt the Everfrost peaks well into 7th level, and then the tundra can take them through 15th with nary a wit o' trouble or boredom.  And as to the tailor mentioned above who collects the white bear pelts, Cindl be her name.  She's a bonny lass, my third cousin on me father's side she is...<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:jivingpoo@ticnet.com">Panoyen</a> of The Tribunal on Nov. 10, 1999 at 11:43pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">I haven't spent much time at all here, but I can still add some info. Polar bear cubs are good to hunt at lvl 3 to 5 and sometimes have Polar Bear Skins. You can sell these for about 1pp each to players because they are needed for the Polar Bear Cloaks. Also, you can turn these in to one of the tailors in Halas. I can't remember her name but you can of course hail her and find out if she is the one or not. Well, this is really really good exp at low levels, and it yields a piece of large tattered (PW) armor with each skin.<br><br></td></tr>
